  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I keep Instagram private from Facebook friends and contacts?",
  "response": "If you want to keep your Instagram account private from your Facebook friends and contacts, you can take several steps:\n\n1. **Unlink Accounts (if previously connected):**\n   - **Open Instagram:** Go to your profile.\n   - **Access Settings:** Tap the three lines (menu icon) in the upper-right corner, then select \"Settings.\"\n   - **Account Center:** Tap on \"Accounts Center\" at the bottom.\n   - **Accounts & Profiles:** Tap on \"Accounts & Profiles\" and unlink your Facebook account from your Instagram account.\n\n2. **Set Instagram Account to Private:**\n   - **Open Instagram:** Navigate to your profile.\n   - **Access Settings:** Tap the three lines (menu icon) in the upper-right corner, then go to \"Settings.\"\n   - **Privacy Settings:** Tap on \u201cPrivacy.\u201d\n   - **Account Privacy:** Toggle on \u201cPrivate Account.\u201d This ensures only approved followers can see your posts.\n\n3. **Adjust Contact Syncing:**\n   - **Open Instagram:** Go to your profile.\n   - **Access Settings:** Tap the three lines (menu icon) in the upper-right corner, then select \"Settings.\"\n   - **Account:** Tap on \u201cAccount,\u201d then \u201cContacts Syncing.\u201d\n   - **Disable Syncing:** Turn off \u201cConnect Contacts\u201d to prevent Instagram from accessing your contacts.\n\n4. **Review Connected Apps and Services:**\n   - Make sure you have reviewed any connected third-party apps through both Instagram and Facebook that might share data between the two platforms.\n\n5. **Manage Facebook\u2019s Friend Suggestions:**\n   - **On Facebook Website:** Go to your Facebook profile settings, and navigate to \u201cPrivacy.\u201d\n   - **Friend Suggestions:** Here, you can limit how people use your contact info to find you, which might reduce Instagram account suggestions.\n\n6. **Be Mindful During Sign-Up:**\n   - If you are setting up a new Instagram account, use a different email and phone number than those associated with your Facebook account.\n\nBy following these steps, you can better manage your privacy on Instagram and limit visibility to your Facebook contacts and friends.",
